WEBVTT

1
00:00:18.480 --> 00:00:20.480
[gentle. eerie music]

2
00:00:36.480 --> 00:00:38.080
[cat mews. bell tinkles]

3
00:00:43.800 --> 00:00:45.640
[dramatic music]

4
00:00:47.880 --> 00:00:50.600
[pulsating dramatic music]

5
00:01:04.240 --> 00:01:06.800
["The Feminine Urge"
by The Last Dinner Party plays]

6
00:01:40.640 --> 00:01:42.080
{\an8}[bell rings]

7
00:02:06.120 --> 00:02:07.800
[song fades]

8
00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:14.520
Why are you hiding?
You need to be eyes on Penton.

9
00:02:14.600 --> 00:02:17.920
Mrs. Penton is never gonna serve you
if she knows your birthday.

10
00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:22.720
Well. she's not currently on till.
and... I have this.

11
00:02:25.240 --> 00:02:26.960
This makes you 27!

12
00:02:27.040 --> 00:02:28.040
I can pull it off.

13
00:02:28.560 --> 00:02:30.840
Pip. you need to distract
Mrs. Penton. okay?

14
00:02:30.920 --> 00:02:32.880
Do not let her look at the till.

15
00:02:32.960 --> 00:02:34.760
- Why me?
- You got this!

16
00:02:34.840 --> 00:02:36.520
I don't want to be an accessory
to a crime!

17
00:02:36.560 --> 00:02:38.240
Well. don't fuck it up.

18
00:02:45.160 --> 00:02:46.680
[clears throat quietly]

19
00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:52.960
[girl] There we are.

20
00:02:54.800 --> 00:02:56.000
Hi!

21
00:02:57.000 --> 00:02:58.000
Hi.

22
00:03:04.200 --> 00:03:08.680
I just... I had a question
I wanted to ask you.

23
00:03:08.760 --> 00:03:10.040
Um...

24
00:03:13.680 --> 00:03:15.640
Are you here as some kind of a decoy?

25
00:03:18.640 --> 00:03:19.640
Yes.

26
00:03:20.360 --> 00:03:23.360
- Pippa Fitz-Amobi!
- Come on!

27
00:03:26.160 --> 00:03:28.240
Bye! Sorry!

28
00:03:28.880 --> 00:03:30.080
[boy] Let's go home.

29
00:03:33.600 --> 00:03:35.680
[chatting indistinctly]

30
00:03:45.240 --> 00:03:46.520
[bell tolls]

31
00:03:48.520 --> 00:03:49.760
[bell tolls]

32
00:03:51.840 --> 00:03:52.840
[bell tolls]

33
00:04:14.320 --> 00:04:17.400
[Victor] After everyone telling me there
wasn't a hope of getting him off.

34
00:04:17.480 --> 00:04:21.120
justice had finally been served.
And do you know why?

35
00:04:21.200 --> 00:04:23.600
- 'Cause you followed due process.
- Exactly.

36
00:04:23.680 --> 00:04:26.800
Innocent until proven guilty. Unless...

37
00:04:26.880 --> 00:04:27.920
You're a Black man.

38
00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:29.160
Vic?

39
00:04:32.200 --> 00:04:34.200
Have we got any of the posh crisps?

40
00:04:34.280 --> 00:04:37.296
[Leanne] No. because they cost a fortune.
You can buy some when you get a job.

41
00:04:37.320 --> 00:04:40.640
Actually. in fact.
Linda Walker's catering company

42
00:04:40.720 --> 00:04:43.080
is looking for waitresses over the summer.

43
00:04:43.160 --> 00:04:45.920
She's organizing some big do

44
00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:49.960
for the Hastings' silver wedding
anniversary party or something.

45
00:04:51.280 --> 00:04:54.560
What's that? Vic's cooking dinner.

46
00:04:54.640 --> 00:04:58.400
It's a starter!
Got homework to do.

47
00:04:58.480 --> 00:05:01.640
It's the first day of the holidays.
What homework could you possibly have?

48
00:05:01.720 --> 00:05:05.200
Uh. my EPQ? It's really important. Dad.

49
00:05:05.280 --> 00:05:06.640
Ah.

50
00:05:06.720 --> 00:05:08.720
Well. first you need to walk the dog.

51
00:05:14.760 --> 00:05:16.800
- [commotion]
- [boy] Hurry up. man.

52
00:05:18.760 --> 00:05:19.760
Knock it loud.

53
00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:23.440
[pounding on door]

54
00:05:24.840 --> 00:05:28.280
Hey. idiots! You dropped
your communal brain cell!

55
00:05:28.360 --> 00:05:30.160
- [boy 2] Let's go!
- [boy 1] Go! Move!

56
00:05:30.240 --> 00:05:31.400
[boys laughing]

57
00:06:04.320 --> 00:06:06.280
- [Sal] Hey. Pip.
- Hi.

58
00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:14.120
Have you seen Andie?

59
00:06:17.400 --> 00:06:19.600
It's okay. I just...

60
00:06:19.680 --> 00:06:21.840
I just need to speak
to her about something.

61
00:06:42.640 --> 00:06:45.880
There better be a good reason why
I'm not watching <i>Love Island</i> right now.

62
00:06:46.720 --> 00:06:49.240
I've decided what I'm doing my EPQ on.

63
00:06:49.320 --> 00:06:51.560
I'm going to solve the Andie Bell case.

64
00:06:51.640 --> 00:06:55.160
Not this again.
The Andie Bell case is solved.

65
00:06:55.240 --> 00:06:57.000
Her boyfriend killed her. remember?

66
00:06:57.080 --> 00:07:00.480
The whole world thinks Sal Singh
is guilty. but he never had a trial

67
00:07:00.560 --> 00:07:02.360
and they never even found Andie's body.

68
00:07:02.440 --> 00:07:05.360
Except Sal confessed to her murder
and then killed himself.

69
00:07:05.440 --> 00:07:08.600
Do you know how many people confessed
to the murder of Charles Lindbergh Jr.?

70
00:07:08.680 --> 00:07:11.120
- I have no idea who that even is.
- Two hundred.

71
00:07:11.200 --> 00:07:13.920
That's 199 false confessions.

72
00:07:14.880 --> 00:07:16.960
Come on. You knew Sal. too.

73
00:07:17.040 --> 00:07:19.600
He was head boy.
he was going to Cambridge.

74
00:07:20.480 --> 00:07:22.320
And he was always really nice to me.

75
00:07:22.920 --> 00:07:24.600
Sal was a good guy.

76
00:07:24.680 --> 00:07:26.440
Good guys don't kill people.

77
00:07:26.520 --> 00:07:28.560
Well. actually. they do.
All the time.

78
00:07:29.200 --> 00:07:31.040
What is it with you and this case?

79
00:07:32.040 --> 00:07:33.800
And if Sal didn't do it. who did?

80
00:07:33.880 --> 00:07:37.600
I don't know yet. But whoever it was
might still be out there.

81
00:07:43.960 --> 00:07:47.200
["A New Error" by Moderat plays]

82
00:08:06.520 --> 00:08:09.280
[DI Hawkins] <i>Andie was last seen
driving away</i>

83
00:08:09.360 --> 00:08:13.960
{\an8}<i>from her home on Church Street
at approximately 10:30 p.m.</i>

84
00:08:14.960 --> 00:08:18.640
<i>CCTV footage from Little Kilton Square</i>

85
00:08:18.720 --> 00:08:23.440
<i>shows Andie driving past at 10:38 p.m.</i>

86
00:08:24.320 --> 00:08:28.360
[news reporter] <i>When Andie Bell failed
to pick her parents up from a dinner party</i>

87
00:08:28.440 --> 00:08:31.680
<i>at the agreed time of 12:45 a.m..</i>

88
00:08:31.760 --> 00:08:35.000
{\an8}<i>Jason and Dawn Bell became concerned.</i>

89
00:08:37.560 --> 00:08:41.560
{\an8}<i>It's been five days since Andie Bell
went missing from her home.</i>

90
00:08:41.640 --> 00:08:45.840
{\an8}<i>Late yesterday. a body
was discovered in woodland.</i>

91
00:08:45.920 --> 00:08:48.720
{\an8}<i>close to the village of Little Kilton.</i>

92
00:08:48.800 --> 00:08:52.480
{\an8}<i>It is believed to be that
of 18-year-old Salil Singh.</i>

93
00:08:52.560 --> 00:08:55.600
<i>the boyfriend of missing teenager
Andie Bell.</i>

94
00:08:55.680 --> 00:08:57.880
[news reporter 1] <i>It is believed
Salil took his own life</i>

95
00:08:57.920 --> 00:09:00.040
<i>after confessing to
the murder of his girlfriend.</i>

96
00:09:00.120 --> 00:09:04.080
[female reporter] <i>His younger brother Ravi
was the last person to see him alive.</i>

97
00:09:04.160 --> 00:09:07.360
<i>Jason and Dawn Bell remain
unable to bury their daughter.</i>

98
00:09:07.440 --> 00:09:10.480
<i>as the search continues for Andie's body.</i>

99
00:09:12.800 --> 00:09:14.880
[bird cooing]

100
00:09:21.280 --> 00:09:23.680
[vehicle approaching]

101
00:09:48.800 --> 00:09:50.200
Hi.

102
00:09:50.280 --> 00:09:51.960
Do I know you?

103
00:09:53.080 --> 00:09:55.080
No. Just taking a walk.

104
00:09:59.440 --> 00:10:01.280
[chuckles] With muffins.

105
00:10:01.360 --> 00:10:02.520
[chuckles softly]

106
00:10:02.600 --> 00:10:03.840
Okay.

107
00:10:09.680 --> 00:10:11.440
Are you sure I can't help you
with something?

108
00:10:11.480 --> 00:10:14.040
Well. how do you know
I'm not just heading this way?

109
00:10:17.400 --> 00:10:18.880
Do I remember you from school?

110
00:10:18.960 --> 00:10:21.600
You did that assembly
dressed as Florence Nightingale.

111
00:10:21.680 --> 00:10:25.640
Ugh... Emmeline Pankhurst. but...
yes. that was me.

112
00:10:25.720 --> 00:10:27.440
That explains it.
I was wondering why

113
00:10:27.520 --> 00:10:29.960
Florence Nightingale would
chain herself to the gym apparatus.

114
00:10:30.040 --> 00:10:32.200
Yeah. that didn't quite go as planned.

115
00:10:32.280 --> 00:10:34.560
Took them two and a half hours
to cut me free.

116
00:10:38.760 --> 00:10:40.400
[Ravi] Who's this handsome boy?

117
00:10:40.480 --> 00:10:41.920
[Pip] His name's Barney.

118
00:10:43.400 --> 00:10:45.240
- Vanilla essence?
- Yes.

119
00:10:47.520 --> 00:10:50.720
- Hmm... Touch of nutmeg?
- [scoffs] You're good.

120
00:10:50.800 --> 00:10:53.240
Okay. did I use
fresh or frozen blueberries?

121
00:10:53.320 --> 00:10:56.240
- Both?
- Muffin genius.

122
00:10:56.320 --> 00:10:57.680
Why. thank you.

123
00:10:58.440 --> 00:11:00.080
So. pedestrian with muffins...

124
00:11:01.160 --> 00:11:03.080
- this is me.
- I'm Pip.

125
00:11:03.160 --> 00:11:05.840
I've actually been wanting to come by
and talk to you about my EPQ

126
00:11:05.920 --> 00:11:09.360
and so these are kind of...
bribery muffins.

127
00:11:09.920 --> 00:11:11.040
Your what?

128
00:11:11.120 --> 00:11:14.480
Yeah. I don't know if when you
were at school. if you had do an EPQ.

129
00:11:14.560 --> 00:11:17.960
Anyway. we do. which everyone's
really annoyed about apart from me.

130
00:11:18.040 --> 00:11:20.560
It's an Extended Project Qualification
I need to do

131
00:11:20.640 --> 00:11:22.000
for my university application.

132
00:11:22.720 --> 00:11:24.880
I was gonna do a feminist analysis
of the gothic novel.

133
00:11:24.920 --> 00:11:27.960
but then I thought.
"What's something that really matters?"

134
00:11:28.040 --> 00:11:31.720
Which is when I thought of
the Andie Bell case. and your brother.

135
00:11:31.800 --> 00:11:34.560
So. yeah. I guess that's what I'm doing.

136
00:11:34.640 --> 00:11:36.736
and I was wondering if
I could ask you some questions.

137
00:11:36.760 --> 00:11:38.400
- Oh. wow. I think you should go.
- But...

138
00:11:38.440 --> 00:11:39.480
My brother's dead.

139
00:11:44.240 --> 00:11:46.160
[door lock clicks. opens]

140
00:11:48.560 --> 00:11:51.120
[somber music]

141
00:12:24.240 --> 00:12:27.080
{\an8}[birds chittering]

142
00:12:33.920 --> 00:12:36.680
[ominous music]

143
00:13:00.440 --> 00:13:02.600
[music continues]

144
00:13:48.080 --> 00:13:49.720
[Barney barks]

145
00:13:53.880 --> 00:13:55.000
Come on.

146
00:13:58.880 --> 00:14:00.000
Hey!

147
00:14:02.440 --> 00:14:03.440
Hey!

148
00:14:05.840 --> 00:14:07.760
[tense music]

149
00:14:09.480 --> 00:14:11.760
[Barney continues barking]

150
00:14:16.280 --> 00:14:18.040
[panting]

151
00:14:31.400 --> 00:14:33.160
[Becca] Cute dog. [laughs]

152
00:14:36.680 --> 00:14:38.520
Sorry. did I scare you?

153
00:14:39.080 --> 00:14:40.880
Just thought you were someone else.

154
00:14:43.160 --> 00:14:44.560
Don't worry.

155
00:14:45.560 --> 00:14:47.320
People always get us confused.

156
00:14:59.960 --> 00:15:02.200
[Lauren sighs]

157
00:15:03.960 --> 00:15:06.320
So much for the summer of love.

158
00:15:11.000 --> 00:15:12.760
{\an8}Hey. Cara. is Naomi home?

159
00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:16.040
- Pip. no.
- [Pip] What?

160
00:15:16.120 --> 00:15:18.480
Please don't ask my sister about Sal.

161
00:15:18.560 --> 00:15:19.800
Why not?

162
00:15:20.200 --> 00:15:22.800
She was with him
the night Andie went missing.

163
00:15:22.880 --> 00:15:26.760
She's a key witness.
Max is in Italy and Jake moved away.

164
00:15:26.840 --> 00:15:28.200
No way.

165
00:15:29.560 --> 00:15:30.880
Okay.

166
00:15:30.960 --> 00:15:33.600
You do realize
how sensitive this still is. Pip?

167
00:15:35.560 --> 00:15:37.480
Yeah. 'course I do.

168
00:15:39.720 --> 00:15:41.760
[Lauren] Oh. my God.

169
00:15:41.840 --> 00:15:44.640
Ant Lowe has just asked me
to go to the Hastings' party with him.

170
00:15:44.720 --> 00:15:45.720
[Cara] No!

171
00:15:45.760 --> 00:15:47.840
- [both squeal]
- What will you say?

172
00:15:47.920 --> 00:15:50.640
Uh... yes. obviously!

173
00:15:51.400 --> 00:15:53.600
Ant's an idiot.

174
00:15:53.680 --> 00:15:57.080
He always says "pacifically"
when he means "specifically."

175
00:15:57.160 --> 00:15:58.400
Don't listen to Pip.

176
00:15:58.480 --> 00:16:01.800
The last guy she had a crush on
has been dead for. like. 200 years.

177
00:16:01.880 --> 00:16:03.800
- Who?
- [both] Nikola Tesla.

178
00:16:04.520 --> 00:16:06.680
Anyway. who wants snacks?

179
00:16:06.760 --> 00:16:09.120
- Um. okay.
- [Cara] Yes. please.

180
00:16:10.360 --> 00:16:13.800
[Cara and Lauren laughing.
chatting]

181
00:16:21.200 --> 00:16:22.760
[hinges squeak softly]

182
00:16:40.200 --> 00:16:41.880
[clock chimes softly]

183
00:16:41.960 --> 00:16:43.640
[gentle music playing]

184
00:16:46.320 --> 00:16:47.320
[clock chimes softly]

185
00:16:57.920 --> 00:16:59.000
[clock chimes softly]

186
00:17:09.280 --> 00:17:10.560
[clock chimes softly]

187
00:17:16.160 --> 00:17:17.800
- Hey. Gnome.
- Shit!

188
00:17:18.600 --> 00:17:20.920
- You okay?
- You scared me. that's all.

189
00:17:23.280 --> 00:17:24.760
How's the job hunt going?

190
00:17:24.840 --> 00:17:26.680
[Naomi] Still hunting.

191
00:17:31.640 --> 00:17:33.520
Did you guys take the Jammie Dodgers?

192
00:17:34.040 --> 00:17:35.080
No.

193
00:17:35.160 --> 00:17:38.160
I saw Dad unpacking them earlier.
but they've vanished.

194
00:17:38.480 --> 00:17:41.720
Things don't just vanish.
They must be here. Keep looking.

195
00:17:42.440 --> 00:17:46.800
Sometimes things do disappear.
Like hairbands. odd socks.

196
00:17:46.880 --> 00:17:50.120
Well. with socks. you simply check them
on the way into the washing machine

197
00:17:50.200 --> 00:17:52.240
and then you check them on the way out.

198
00:17:52.320 --> 00:17:53.680
It's not rocket science.

199
00:17:55.560 --> 00:17:57.680
You never give up on anything.
do you. Pip?

200
00:18:00.480 --> 00:18:02.480
- Hey. Naomi.
- Mm-hmm.

201
00:18:03.280 --> 00:18:08.280
Did Cara tell you I decided
to do my EPQ on the Andie Bell case?

202
00:18:12.480 --> 00:18:13.480
No.

203
00:18:13.560 --> 00:18:17.960
Well. I just wondered
if I could ask you some questions.

204
00:18:18.760 --> 00:18:21.800
Seeing as you and Sal
were so close and everything.

205
00:18:25.120 --> 00:18:28.160
Sure. if I can remember stuff.

206
00:18:29.560 --> 00:18:31.600
- Five years is a long time.
- [phone beeps]

207
00:18:32.720 --> 00:18:34.400
Is it okay if I record it?

208
00:18:38.120 --> 00:18:43.280
[clears throat] Interview one.
Naomi Ward. Sal's best friend.

209
00:18:44.720 --> 00:18:46.960
Could you tell me
everything that you remember

210
00:18:47.040 --> 00:18:50.640
about the events of the night
of Friday. the 19th of April 2019?

211
00:18:52.840 --> 00:18:54.280
Um...

212
00:18:54.360 --> 00:18:59.120
We were all at Max's playing
<i>Super Mario Party.</i> Sal left early.

213
00:19:00.160 --> 00:19:01.720
Who's "we"?

214
00:19:02.480 --> 00:19:04.120
Jake. Max. Sal. and me.

215
00:19:04.200 --> 00:19:06.600
And what time did Sal leave exactly?

216
00:19:06.680 --> 00:19:08.280
10:30 p.m.

217
00:19:08.960 --> 00:19:11.080
I remember 'cause we ordered a pizza.

218
00:19:11.160 --> 00:19:13.760
Sal left just as the delivery guy arrived.

219
00:19:14.400 --> 00:19:16.200
He said he was tired.

220
00:19:16.280 --> 00:19:17.800
[Cara] Pip! Where are you?

221
00:19:17.880 --> 00:19:19.400
Just coming!

222
00:19:20.640 --> 00:19:23.320
But he didn't get back home until 12:50.

223
00:19:27.280 --> 00:19:29.320
I don't know what you want me to say.

224
00:19:29.400 --> 00:19:31.240
Sal was a smart guy.

225
00:19:31.320 --> 00:19:33.360
If he'd killed Andie.
you'd have thought

226
00:19:33.440 --> 00:19:35.800
he would have at least
come up with an alibi.

227
00:19:36.600 --> 00:19:37.800
[Cara. yelling] Pip!

228
00:19:40.520 --> 00:19:41.960
Sal had an alibi.

229
00:19:44.400 --> 00:19:46.480
- [door opens]
- [Elliot] Hey. Pip.

230
00:19:46.560 --> 00:19:48.920
- Hi. Dad.
- [Elliot] Hi. my love.

231
00:19:50.520 --> 00:19:51.600
How's the Internet?

232
00:19:52.520 --> 00:19:54.000
Weird and depressing.

233
00:19:54.080 --> 00:19:56.120
So. no change there. then.

234
00:19:56.640 --> 00:19:57.920
How's tutoring?

235
00:19:58.480 --> 00:20:02.360
Boring... but a teacher's salary
only stretches so far.

236
00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:06.240
- Join us for dinner. Pip?
- Not for me. thanks.

237
00:20:06.320 --> 00:20:09.880
Victor's making tacos.
a whole Mexican feast.

238
00:20:09.960 --> 00:20:12.520
Okay. <i>Â¡Que. hombre!</i>

239
00:20:16.400 --> 00:20:19.320
Hey. Pip. don't forget your notebook.

240
00:20:30.080 --> 00:20:32.640
[suspenseful music]

241
00:21:25.360 --> 00:21:27.720
[suspenseful music continues]

242
00:22:02.080 --> 00:22:06.320
Barney was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize
for services to humanity.

243
00:22:06.400 --> 00:22:08.760
the First Bearded Collie
ever to do so.

244
00:22:08.840 --> 00:22:15.280
That year he made the front cover
of <i>Time</i> magazine.

245
00:22:15.360 --> 00:22:19.360
and guess what three words
were printed underneath his picture?

246
00:22:19.440 --> 00:22:23.440
- "Stay beardy. folks."
- "Stay beardy. folks."

247
00:22:23.520 --> 00:22:25.480
Yes. you're asleep.

248
00:22:25.560 --> 00:22:29.520
Your dad used to tell you that one. only
it was Beetle the Wonderdog back then.

249
00:22:29.600 --> 00:22:31.600
Don't tell Josh.

250
00:22:31.680 --> 00:22:33.280
Don't remember.

251
00:22:33.360 --> 00:22:36.640
I've been thinking about
what you said about getting a job.

252
00:22:36.720 --> 00:22:39.960
and I think you're right.
Need to get out in the real world.

253
00:22:40.040 --> 00:22:42.080
Would you ask Linda
if she still needs waitresses

254
00:22:42.160 --> 00:22:43.960
for the Hastings' silver wedding party?

255
00:22:44.040 --> 00:22:46.760
Yeah. of course.
I am seeing her tomorrow at book club.

256
00:22:46.840 --> 00:22:48.080
so I'll ask her.

257
00:22:49.360 --> 00:22:54.040
Maybe ask if she needs two.
Cara's really keen as well.

258
00:22:54.120 --> 00:22:55.280
Great.

259
00:22:56.440 --> 00:22:58.800
- ["In the Mood" by Glenn Miller playing]
- [chattering]

260
00:22:58.880 --> 00:23:01.040
There are people from school here.

261
00:23:01.120 --> 00:23:03.920
I didn't know there was a whole
Stars of the Silver Screen theme.

262
00:23:04.000 --> 00:23:05.680
Is yours chafing?
Mine's really chafing.

263
00:23:05.760 --> 00:23:08.400
I just need to ask Max one thing
and then we can go.

264
00:23:09.960 --> 00:23:13.200
Come on. It's fun.
We're undercover.

265
00:23:13.720 --> 00:23:14.920
Come on.

266
00:23:39.360 --> 00:23:41.280
[indistinct chatter]

267
00:23:45.960 --> 00:23:47.520
Oh...

268
00:23:47.600 --> 00:23:48.840
Thank you very much.

269
00:23:48.920 --> 00:23:50.560
Thank you very much!

270
00:23:51.200 --> 00:23:53.560
[music continues]

271
00:24:07.600 --> 00:24:08.960
[indistinct conversation]

272
00:24:09.040 --> 00:24:11.800
["Down South Camp Meetin'"
by Benny Goodman playing]

273
00:24:14.120 --> 00:24:16.280
[laughter]

274
00:24:25.960 --> 00:24:27.600
[man] Thank you very much.

275
00:24:29.880 --> 00:24:31.280
Thank you.

276
00:24:56.240 --> 00:24:59.480
[Naomi] <i>We were all at Max's
playing</i> Super Mario Party.

277
00:24:59.560 --> 00:25:01.400
[Pip] <i>And what time did Sal leave exactly?</i>

278
00:25:01.480 --> 00:25:03.120
[Naomi] <i>10:30 p.m.</i>

279
00:25:15.480 --> 00:25:17.600
[Jason] You need to come here right now.

280
00:25:18.160 --> 00:25:20.120
Because I'm telling you. Becca.

281
00:25:20.760 --> 00:25:23.440
Becca! Fuck!

282
00:25:26.680 --> 00:25:28.360
Daughters. eh?

283
00:25:29.080 --> 00:25:30.160
[chuckles softly]

284
00:25:31.600 --> 00:25:34.360
[suspenseful music playing]

285
00:25:56.400 --> 00:25:57.760
- [soft thud]
- [gasps]

286
00:26:01.160 --> 00:26:02.960
[suspenseful music continues]

287
00:26:10.720 --> 00:26:11.840
[soft thud]

288
00:26:14.320 --> 00:26:15.360
[Pip] Hello?

289
00:26:19.960 --> 00:26:22.240
[soft thud continues]

290
00:26:28.120 --> 00:26:29.240
Hi.

291
00:26:31.440 --> 00:26:33.200
[Max] You've been stalking me.

292
00:26:34.560 --> 00:26:37.080
[Pip] I'd like to ask you
some questions.

293
00:26:38.640 --> 00:26:41.760
[laughs] It's time for the speeches.

294
00:26:42.520 --> 00:26:44.000
Won't take long.

295
00:26:50.520 --> 00:26:52.160
What are you gonna do for me?

296
00:26:52.960 --> 00:26:54.160
Sorry?

297
00:26:55.280 --> 00:26:57.200
Quid pro quo. you know?

298
00:26:57.880 --> 00:27:01.440
Tell you what. Every time I answer
a question. you have to take a shot.

299
00:27:02.560 --> 00:27:04.320
I don't drink.

300
00:27:04.400 --> 00:27:06.320
Well. that's boring.

301
00:27:09.480 --> 00:27:10.800
[Max grunts softly]

302
00:27:24.440 --> 00:27:26.000
What do you want to know?

303
00:27:26.080 --> 00:27:27.280
[phone beeps]

304
00:27:28.440 --> 00:27:31.280
August 3rd. interview with Max Hastings.

305
00:27:31.640 --> 00:27:33.640
Is this an interrogation?

306
00:27:34.280 --> 00:27:36.680
[Pip] On Friday.
the 19th of April 2019.

307
00:27:36.760 --> 00:27:40.120
Jake. Sal. and Naomi were all at yours
playing <i>Super Mario Party.</i>

308
00:27:40.200 --> 00:27:42.120
It was <i>FIFA.</i> but carry on.

309
00:27:42.200 --> 00:27:44.160
What time did Sal leave?

310
00:27:44.240 --> 00:27:46.680
Mm-mm. Down the hatch.

311
00:27:50.400 --> 00:27:51.680
[coughs]

312
00:27:53.120 --> 00:27:56.880
10:30 p.m.
Look. I don't know what you want.

313
00:27:56.960 --> 00:27:58.640
It was a standard Friday evening.

314
00:27:58.720 --> 00:28:00.840
Jake and I just played
Xbox and got pissed.

315
00:28:00.920 --> 00:28:02.800
What about Naomi?

316
00:28:02.880 --> 00:28:04.120
Naomi was MIA.

317
00:28:04.200 --> 00:28:05.520
What was she doing?

318
00:28:12.280 --> 00:28:15.000
I don't know. Taking a nap.
taking a dump. Fuck knows.

319
00:28:15.080 --> 00:28:17.640
Listen. I have to go watch
my parents pretend

320
00:28:17.720 --> 00:28:20.080
like they've been happily married
for 25 years.

321
00:28:20.840 --> 00:28:23.000
Naomi told me that Sal had an alibi.

322
00:28:26.280 --> 00:28:27.600
What was it?

323
00:28:46.520 --> 00:28:48.160
We were Sal's alibi.

324
00:28:48.840 --> 00:28:50.160
He made us lie for him.

325
00:28:52.720 --> 00:28:55.920
The day after Andie went missing.
Sal asked us to tell the police

326
00:28:56.000 --> 00:28:58.000
that he'd stayed round mine till 12:15.

327
00:28:58.080 --> 00:29:00.080
He said he didn't want them
wasting time on him

328
00:29:00.160 --> 00:29:02.400
when they should be
out there finding Andie.

329
00:29:02.480 --> 00:29:04.240
We went along with him.

330
00:29:05.000 --> 00:29:07.160
Then you told the police the truth?

331
00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:10.360
- Yeah.
- What changed your mind?

332
00:29:10.440 --> 00:29:12.680
It's a crime to lie to the police.

333
00:29:12.760 --> 00:29:16.520
Anyway. things were getting real.
Andie hadn't just shown up.

334
00:29:17.560 --> 00:29:19.280
Did you like Andie?

335
00:29:19.360 --> 00:29:22.200
I didn't know the girl.
Like. literally never spoke to her.

336
00:29:24.920 --> 00:29:27.160
What are you trying to prove
by doing this?

337
00:29:28.600 --> 00:29:30.000
That Sal's innocent.

338
00:29:30.840 --> 00:29:32.320
You really think that?

339
00:29:32.400 --> 00:29:34.080
Don't you?

340
00:29:34.960 --> 00:29:38.920
[scoffs] The Sal I knew.
no way he could have killed her.

341
00:29:41.480 --> 00:29:43.000
But he confessed to it.

342
00:29:44.120 --> 00:29:46.120
Then he went into the woods...

343
00:29:47.400 --> 00:29:49.480
and swallowed a bunch of pills.

344
00:29:50.960 --> 00:29:52.280
I mean...

345
00:29:54.000 --> 00:29:56.000
you don't do that for nothing. do you?

346
00:30:10.000 --> 00:30:13.160
[Toby] People say
money can't buy you love.

347
00:30:13.240 --> 00:30:16.080
Well. they clearly haven't met
my beautiful wife.

348
00:30:16.160 --> 00:30:18.000
- [guests laughing]
- [man] Well said.

349
00:30:18.080 --> 00:30:19.560
[Toby] Seriously. I'm a very...

350
00:30:19.640 --> 00:30:23.240
It's always nice to see true love.
isn't it? Bit of old-school romancing.

351
00:30:26.640 --> 00:30:28.440
I didn't mean to scare you.

352
00:30:29.200 --> 00:30:30.480
It's all right.

353
00:30:32.440 --> 00:30:33.960
A word to the wise.

354
00:30:35.000 --> 00:30:37.440
I've heard you're a bit of a nosy parker.

355
00:30:39.040 --> 00:30:41.720
And you know what happens
to nosy parkers. don't you?

356
00:30:52.160 --> 00:30:54.080
["It Had To Be You" plays]

357
00:30:54.160 --> 00:30:56.960
Naomi's wasted and acting weird.
I've put her in the car.

358
00:30:57.040 --> 00:30:59.240
Lauren's stormed off in tears.
We need to go.

359
00:30:59.320 --> 00:31:00.840
Dark forces are at work here.

360
00:31:00.920 --> 00:31:03.240
A good-looking man
just tried to steal my nose.

361
00:31:03.320 --> 00:31:04.760
What good-looking man?

362
00:31:06.240 --> 00:31:08.320
- Are you drunk?
- [Pip] What?

363
00:31:08.400 --> 00:31:12.960
No. No. I only had five teeny.
tiny drinks. like thimbles.

364
00:31:13.040 --> 00:31:14.960
[laughing] Okay. let's go.

365
00:31:17.680 --> 00:31:20.160
So. two key witnesses that say

366
00:31:20.240 --> 00:31:24.520
that Sal lied about his alibi.
which does not look great.

367
00:31:24.600 --> 00:31:27.200
But... it's just so weird.

368
00:31:27.280 --> 00:31:30.360
There are a million discrepancies
about their accounts of that night.

369
00:31:30.440 --> 00:31:34.000
Max says they were playing <i>FIFA.</i> but Naomi
says they were playing <i>Super Mario Party.</i>

370
00:31:34.080 --> 00:31:36.960
Naomi says she was there the whole
evening. but Max says she was MIA.

371
00:31:37.040 --> 00:31:38.560
You spoke to Naomi?

372
00:31:39.240 --> 00:31:40.880
- I'm sorry.
- I asked you not to.

373
00:31:40.960 --> 00:31:42.640
I specifically asked you not to.

374
00:31:42.720 --> 00:31:44.880
Did you know that Naomi
and the others lied for Sal?

375
00:31:44.960 --> 00:31:46.760
- Yes.
- So why wouldn't you tell me?

376
00:31:46.840 --> 00:31:50.280
It was five years ago. and everyone except
for you wants to forget it ever happened.

377
00:31:50.360 --> 00:31:52.680
It's a key piece of information.
and you're my best friend.

378
00:31:52.760 --> 00:31:53.760
Are you for real?

379
00:31:53.840 --> 00:31:56.656
I didn't tell you because I don't
want you stirring everything up again.

380
00:31:56.680 --> 00:31:57.856
- But it's important!
- To you.

381
00:31:57.880 --> 00:32:00.880
You're totally happy to fuck
everyone else's life up

382
00:32:00.960 --> 00:32:03.440
- just so you can carry on play detective.
- I am not playing!

383
00:32:13.240 --> 00:32:15.200
[gentle piano music]

384
00:32:36.960 --> 00:32:39.160
[music continues]

385
00:32:45.880 --> 00:32:47.320
- [Sal] Hey. Pip.
- Hi.

386
00:33:00.320 --> 00:33:01.840
Have you seen Andie?

387
00:33:05.120 --> 00:33:07.320
It's okay. I just...

388
00:33:07.400 --> 00:33:10.000
I just need to speak to her
about something.

389
00:33:13.040 --> 00:33:14.720
She went in there.

390
00:33:15.960 --> 00:33:17.120
Thanks.

391
00:33:38.000 --> 00:33:39.600
[knocking]

392
00:33:49.320 --> 00:33:50.440
Hi.

393
00:33:51.560 --> 00:33:52.760
Hi.

394
00:33:54.760 --> 00:33:58.120
I have important information for Ravi.

395
00:33:58.760 --> 00:34:01.040
From a galaxy far. far away?

396
00:34:02.600 --> 00:34:05.080
No. I live on Martinsend Way.

397
00:34:06.000 --> 00:34:07.160
Come in.

398
00:34:12.600 --> 00:34:13.720
Sorry.

399
00:34:23.320 --> 00:34:24.720
[Nisha] Ravi?

400
00:34:25.840 --> 00:34:27.680
[footsteps approaching]

401
00:34:32.320 --> 00:34:34.640
She says she has important information.

402
00:34:38.440 --> 00:34:39.600
[Pip] Hi.

403
00:34:41.800 --> 00:34:43.960
I came to tell you something.

404
00:34:44.560 --> 00:34:46.920
Is it that you've
completely lost your mind?

405
00:34:47.800 --> 00:34:49.000
What?

406
00:34:51.040 --> 00:34:52.800
Oh... [chuckles]

407
00:34:53.760 --> 00:34:55.000
But why are you here?

408
00:34:58.920 --> 00:35:01.440
I came to say that I'm sorry.

409
00:35:04.080 --> 00:35:07.360
I want you to know that it wasn't
just a school project for me.

410
00:35:07.440 --> 00:35:09.520
I always believed that Sal was innocent.

411
00:35:10.360 --> 00:35:13.800
So you thought you'd ride in like
some white knight come to save us.

412
00:35:13.880 --> 00:35:16.120
No! No. I didn't think that.

413
00:35:19.120 --> 00:35:22.480
It was just a stupid mistake.
I shouldn't have come.

414
00:35:26.920 --> 00:35:28.080
Hey.

415
00:35:34.640 --> 00:35:36.400
Why did you think he was innocent?

416
00:35:37.560 --> 00:35:40.920
I knew Sal.
He was always kind to me.

417
00:35:43.440 --> 00:35:46.000
He would never have done
anything to hurt her.

418
00:35:49.240 --> 00:35:50.560
Come with me.

419
00:36:18.760 --> 00:36:21.040
[somber music]

420
00:36:44.800 --> 00:36:45.920
It's Sal's.

421
00:36:59.680 --> 00:37:01.160
The confession.

422
00:37:02.920 --> 00:37:05.600
"It was me.
I did it. I'm so sorry."

423
00:37:15.280 --> 00:37:19.160
The grammar. The last text.
punctuation is perfect. but the others...

424
00:37:19.240 --> 00:37:22.720
Sal was the smartest person I knew.
but he texted like an illiterate.

425
00:37:28.640 --> 00:37:30.360
He didn't write the confession.

426
00:37:32.000 --> 00:37:33.720
So if he didn't write it. who did?

427
00:37:34.720 --> 00:37:36.720
I guess that's what we need to find out.

428
00:37:42.600 --> 00:37:45.160
["Gunshot" by Lykke Li plays]

429
00:38:38.280 --> 00:38:39.800
[rain falling]

430
00:38:39.880 --> 00:38:41.280
[no audible dialogue]

431
00:38:42.160 --> 00:38:45.640
[Sal] I can't. I can't... Andie. please.
Please just stop!

432
00:38:45.720 --> 00:38:48.320
[Andie. crying] No. wait.
No. I'm sorry. I love you.

433
00:38:51.120 --> 00:38:52.640
Sal!

434
00:38:56.880 --> 00:38:58.480
I'm sorry.

435
00:39:05.960 --> 00:39:07.400
I'm sorry.

436
00:39:07.480 --> 00:39:08.760
I love you.

437
00:39:08.840 --> 00:39:10.960
I won't say anything else... [indistinct]
okay.

438
00:39:11.040 --> 00:39:12.160
I'm sorry.

439
00:39:12.240 --> 00:39:15.560
["Gunshot" by Lykke Li continues]

440
00:39:27.520 --> 00:39:30.400
["Gunshot" by Lykke Li continues]
